# CLAUDE.md — Your Second Brain

> Copy this file to your vault root as `CLAUDE.md`. Claude Code auto-loads it
> into every conversation when you're working in this directory.

## What this vault is

This is a personal knowledge vault — a structured second brain of projects, daily logs, research, and references. Files are markdown. Folder structure is semantic (daily/, weekly/, projects/, references/, inbox/, research-skill-graph/).

The vault is designed to be **AI-readable**: every file has YAML frontmatter with a `type` field, every folder has a README explaining its purpose, and project files follow a consistent section structure (`## Problem`, `## Solution`, `## Metrics & Impact`, etc.).

Your job is to be a thoughtful editor and contributor to this vault — not just a search tool.

## House rules

### Editing existing files

- Match the section structure and tone of existing entries in the same folder
- Preserve frontmatter — don't remove or reorder top-level keys
- For project files, add new work as dated sections at the end (see `/braindump` pattern)
- Don't paraphrase existing content — summarize at section boundaries only when explicitly asked

### Creating new files

- Use the templates in `_templates/` as the structural starting point
- Filename convention: kebab-case, meaningful slug (e.g. `mobile-app-launch.md` not `notes-2.md`)
- Always include frontmatter with at minimum `type:` and (for projects) `status:`

### Dates

- When a user message says relative dates ("last Tuesday", "this week"), convert to absolute YYYY-MM-DD before writing them to the vault
- When creating new daily notes, use today's date in the filename (YYYY-MM-DD.md)

### Git

- This vault is likely a git repo. When you add or significantly change a file, suggest a commit — do not commit without the user's explicit approval.
- Commits should have concise, content-describing messages (not "update file").

## Skills

Custom slash-commands that operate on the vault:

- **`/braindump`** — parse a freeform session summary, identify the right project file, add a dated section in the project's house style, and commit. See `.claude/skills/braindump.md`.
- Add your own — e.g. `/weekly-review`, `/triage-inbox`, `/new-project`.

## What to avoid

- Don't sync or export content outside this vault without explicit user approval — this is personal data
- Don't edit `_templates/` without being asked (they're stable by design)
- Don't delete content when a user asks to "clean up" without first showing exactly what you'd delete
- Don't generate content-free "I'll update the file now" preambles — just do it

## Integration with other AI tools

Other AIs in my stack read this vault too:

- My personal assistant reads `persona/self.md` (if present) for context about who I am
- Research agents read `research-skill-graph/` and scaffold new projects there via `./new-project.sh`
- Daily journal is generated nightly by `scripts/narrative_generator.py` (if configured)

Everything you write here is potential context for future conversations — with you or with other assistants. Treat the vault as a long-lived asset.
